<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <prefix>§</prefix>
  <num>28:12-201</num>
  <heading proof="needed">Definitions.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>In <cite path="28|I|12|2">this part</cite>, the term:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>"Adjustment date" means July 1, 2025, or the date that is one year after April 20, 2024, whichever is later.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>"<cite path="28|I|12">Article 12</cite> property" means a controllable account, controllable electronic record, or controllable payment intangible.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(3)</num>
      <text>"<cite doc="D.C. Law 25-158" path="§2">2024 Act</cite>" means the Uniform Commercial Code Amendment Act of 2024, passed on 2nd reading on February 6, 2024 (Enrolled version of B25-5).</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>The following definitions in other articles of <cite path="28|I">this subtitle</cite> apply to <cite path="28|I|12|2">this part</cite>.</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>"Controllable account" <cite path="§28:9-102">§ 28:9-102</cite>.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>"Controllable electronic record" <cite path="§28:12-102">§ 28:12-102</cite>.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(3)</num>
      <text>"Controllable payment intangible" <cite path="§28:9-102">§ 28:9-102</cite>.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(4)</num>
      <text>"Electronic money" <cite path="§28:9-102">§ 28:9-102</cite>.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(5)</num>
      <text>"Financing statement" <cite path="§28:9-102">§ 28:9-102</cite>.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
